    "answer_id" : 15796878,
    "question_id" : 15796855,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You need to configure your environment variables, <code>JAVA_HOME</code> and <code>PATH</code>.</p>\n\n<p><code>JAVA_HOME</code> must contain the path to java, and you should add <strong>%JAVA_HOME%\\bin</strong> to <code>PATH</code></p>\n\n<p>Alternatively, you can simply add to your <code>PATH</code> the whole path to the bin folder, without the <code>JAVA_HOME</code> variable, however, this makes a little more annoying when you need to have more than one java version on your machine (that way you only need to change <code>JAVA_HOME</code> and don't even bother with <code>PATH</code>)</p>\n"
  }, {
